 **Viewer rule:** walk `@instanceDefinitionGeometry`, apply
 `meshVisibleForMode`, render the subset.
 
+### Clamp filter (“with clamps” / “without clamps”)
+
+Clamp meshes are always published with the fixture (same pattern as modes —
+publish all, filter at import). Every clamp mesh and part collection carries:
+
+```json
+{
+  "partTag": "CLAMP",
+  "isClamp": true,
+  "modeGeometryIds": []
+}
+```
+
+Root Collection `properties` and `FixtureType` also advertise:
+
+```json
+{
+  "hasClamps": true,
+  "clampPartIds": ["rebus-clamp-part", "rebus-clamp-part-2"],
+  "clampPartCount": 2
+}
+```
+
+Connector import UI should offer **With clamps** / **Without clamps** when
+`hasClamps` is true (or when any mesh has `partTag === "CLAMP"` /
+`isClamp === true`):
+
+```javascript
+function meshVisibleForClamps(mesh, includeClamps) {
+  if (includeClamps) return true;
+  if (mesh.isClamp === true) return false;
+  return mesh.partTag !== 'CLAMP';
+}
+
+const visibleMeshes = allDefinitionMeshes
+  .filter((m) => meshVisibleForMode(m, selectedMode.geometryRoot))
+  .filter((m) => meshVisibleForClamps(m, includeClamps));
+```
+
